.TH LPF-APPLY 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.1" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-apply \- apply a plan with confirmation and rollback support
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf apply <policy> [\-\-confirm <duration>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Apply a checked policy using the typed backend plan.
Guarded apply records rollback preimages and automatically rolls back if not confirmed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-confirm <duration>
require confirmation before the duration expires
.TP
\-\-dry\-run
validate and plan without changing host state
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf apply /etc/lpf.conf \-\-confirm 60s
lpf apply /etc/lpf.conf \-\-dry\-run
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Run lpf check and lpf plan before applying host changes.
Use guarded apply with an explicit confirmation window for remote hosts.
Keep rollback evidence server\-side; never rely on browser\-only state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-confirm(8), lpf\-rollback(8), lpf\-history(8)
